## Why This Is Asked
This question evaluates the ability to design cross-cloud, multi-tenant data operations with stringent governance and data contracts.

## Key Concepts
- Delta Live Tables with CDC-like MERGE for incremental updates
- Unity Catalog RBAC and masking for Delta Sharing
- Per-file provenance tracking via an AuditFiles table
- Schema drift evolution policy for resilient ingestion
- Late data handling with watermarks for event-time processing
- Cross-tenant access validation through isolation testing

## Code Example
```python
import dlt
from pyspark.sql.functions import col, current_timestamp, to_timestamp

@dlt.table
def AuditFiles():
    return (
        spark.readStream.format("cloudFiles")
            .option("cloudFiles.format", "parquet")
            .load("/mnt/multi-tenant-logs")
            .withColumn("ingest_ts", current_timestamp())
            .select("_metadata.*", "ingest_ts", "tenant_id")
    )

@dlt.table
def BronzeIngest():
    return dlt.readStream("AuditFiles")

@dlt.table
def SilverLayer():
    return (
        dlt.apply_changes(
            target="silver_events",
            source="BronzeIngest",
            keys=["event_id"],
            sequence_by="event_timestamp",
            ignore_null_updates=False
        )
    )

@dlt.table
def GoldView():
    return (
        spark.read.table("silver_events")
            .groupBy("tenant_id")
            .agg(
                count("event_id").alias("event_count"),
                min("event_timestamp").alias("first_event"),
                max("event_timestamp").alias("last_event")
            )
    )

# Unity Catalog RBAC
GRANT SELECT ON TABLE silver_events TO `tenant-a-admins`;
GRANT SELECT ON TABLE gold_view TO `tenant-a-analysts`;

# Delta Sharing with masking
CREATE SHARE tenant_a_share;
ALTER SHARE tenant_a_share ADD TABLE silver_events;
ALTER SHARE tenant_a_share ADD COLUMN tenant_id;
```

